@startuml risk_level_to_scc_cruise_modulation_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Risk Level To SCC Cruise Modulation Signal Flow\n(NAV/decel/fail-safe context -> SCC cruise state and set-speed modulation)

participant "NAV / decel /\nalert context" as CruiseCtx #F4F7FB
participant "SCC\ncruise owner" as SCC #E8F7E8
participant "Cruise state bus" as CruiseBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / longitudinal users" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Cruise Inputs ==

CruiseCtx -> SCC : speedLimit\nriskLevel\nfailSafeMode\nemergencyContext\nselectedAlertLevel\nvehicleSpeed
SCC -> SCC : default cruiseSetSpeed = speedLimit
SCC -> SCC : if driveState == D and failSafeMode == 0\nthen auto-enable cruiseState = 1
SCC -> SCC : if risk >= 70 or alert >= 6 or emergencyContext > 0\nthen cruiseState = 2, gap = 3, setSpeed = vehicleSpeed - 10
SCC -> SCC : else if risk >= 40 or alert >= 4\nthen cruiseState = 2, gap = 3, setSpeed = vehicleSpeed - 5
note right of SCC
Representative gating inputs
- speedLimit
- riskLevel
- failSafeMode
- emergencyContext / selectedAlertLevel
- vehicleSpeed
end note

== Cruise Publish ==

SCC -> CruiseBus : frmCruiseStateMsg\nCruiseState / GapLevel / CruiseSetSpeed
SCC -> CruiseBus : Powertrain::cruiseState / cruiseSetSpeed
note right of SCC
Representative outputs
- CruiseState
- GapLevel
- CruiseSetSpeed
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

CruiseBus -> Obs : cruise modulation readback /\nlongitudinal-control consumers

note over CruiseCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. NAV speed-limit and decel/fail-safe context reach SCC
2. SCC modulates cruise state and set speed from perceived risk
3. SCC publishes cruise state, gap, and effective set speed
4. Longitudinal users observe the risk-modulated cruise posture
end note

@enduml
